<title>PORTUGAL: BAA ponders Portugal airport firm sale - paper.</title>
<headline>BAA ponders Portugal airport firm sale - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-07-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Airport Authorities (BAA) is interested in bidding in the planned privatisation of Portuguese airport company ANA-Aeroportos e Navegacao, Diario Economico newspaper reported.</p>
<p>It said it had learned that BAA had been in contact with the Public Works Ministry over the planned selloff.</p>
<p>A consortium comprising BZW and Banco de Fomento e Exterior is studying a restructuring and privatisation model for ANA, which operates Portuguese airports, and expects to value the company. No date has been set for the privatisation of ANA.</p>
<p>Government officials were not immediately available to comment on the newspaper report.</p>
